HEADWORD: Self-conceit
<hw>Self`-con*ceit"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Conceit of
one's self; an overweening opinion of one's powers or
endowments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Egotism</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-conceited</ent>⟦br⟧
